  "prompt": "Why did Pepper Potts leave Tony Stark in Captain America: Civil War? Why wasn\u2019t she in the film?",
  "response": "Pepper Potts, played by Gwyneth Paltrow, did not physically appear in *Captain America: Civil War* (2016), though she was referenced in the film. The absence of Pepper Potts in the movie was primarily due to creative decisions and narrative focus rather than a specific in-universe reason.\n\nIn the film, Tony Stark (Iron Man) mentions that he and Pepper are \"taking a break,\" implying that their relationship is strained at the time. This off-screen explanation aligns with the events of *Iron Man 3* (2013) and *Avengers: Age of Ultron* (2015), where their relationship faced challenges. By *Civil War*, their break is used to emphasize Tony's emotional vulnerability and his motivation for supporting the Sokovia Accords, as he is grappling with guilt over his actions and the fallout from Ultron.\n\nGwyneth Paltrow's reduced screen presence in the Marvel Cinematic Universe (MCU) around this time was also influenced by her own career choices and personal priorities, as well as Marvel Studios' evolving narrative focus on other characters and relationships. Pepper would later return in *Spider-Man: Homecoming* (2017) and play a more significant role in *Avengers: Endgame* (2019). \n\nIn summary, Pepper's absence in *Civil War* was a storytelling choice to highlight Tony's personal struggles and to streamline the film's plot.",
